{
  "texts": [
    "Lattice-Complete Principal FramesSince principal frames are always based on Boolean lattices, an important special case is the following.Definition 4.46 (Lattice-Complete Principal Frames).",
    "A principal possibil- ity frame F = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P ⟩ is lattice-complete iff ⟨S ⊥, ⊑ ⊥ ⟩ is a complete Boolean lattice.",
    "◁When ⟨S ⊥, ⊑ ⊥ ⟩ is a complete Boolean lattice, the property characterizing principal frames in Fact 4.41 that i is a total operation on ⟨S ⊥, ⊑ ⊥ ⟩ not only implies the interplay conditions R-rule and R⇒win as in Fact 4.42, but it is also implied by these interplay conditions, as shown by the following.Fact 4.47 (Characterization of Lattice-Complete Principal Frames).",
    "Let F = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P ⟩ be such that ⟨S, ⊑⟩ is a poset, R i is a binary relation on S, and P ⊆ ℘(S).",
    "Then the following are equivalent:1."
  ]
}